{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "medaea-ehr-v1-2026",
    "name": "Medaea EHR API — v1.0.0",
    "description": "Complete Postman collection for the Medaea EHR FastAPI backend.\n\n## Base URL\n`{{base_url}}` = `http://localhost:8000` (dev) or your deployed domain.\n\n## Authentication\nAll protected endpoints require a Bearer JWT token in the Authorization header:\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer {{access_token}}\n```\nRun the **Login** request first — it sets `{{access_token}}` automatically via the Test script.\n\n## Domains\n- Authentication & MFA\n- Users & Profiles\n- Patients\n- Appointments & Calendar\n- Encounters (SOAP notes)\n- Clinical Charting (Allergies, Medications, Problems, Immunizations)\n- Audit Logs\n- Organizations\n\n## Version\n`v1.0.0` — April 2026 — Phase 1 Complete",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json",
    "version": {
      "major": 1,
      "minor": 0,
      "patch": 0
    }
  },
  "variable": [
    { "key": "base_url", "value": "http://localhost:8000", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "access_token", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "patient_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "appointment_id", "value": "", "type": "string" },
    { "key": "encounter_id", "value": "", "type": "string" }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "System",
      "description": "System health and status endpoints",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Health Check",
          "request": {
            "method": "GET",
            "header": [],
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/health", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","health"] },
            "description": "Returns service health status. No authentication required. Useful for uptime monitoring and CI/CD health checks."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK",
              "originalRequest": { "method": "GET", "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/health" } },
              "status": "OK",
              "code": 200,
              "body": "{\"status\": \"ok\", \"service\": \"medaea-fastapi\"}"
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Authentication",
      "description": "Full HIPAA/ONC-compliant auth flow: Signup → Verify Email → Login → MFA → JWT access token.\n\nFlow:\n1. POST /auth/signup\n2. POST /auth/verify-email (if email verification enabled)\n3. POST /auth/login → get JWT\n4. If MFA enabled: POST /auth/mfa/verify → get final JWT",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Signup",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (json.access_token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', json.access_token);",
                  "  }",
                  "  pm.test('Signup successful', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"provider@hospital.org\",\n  \"password\": \"SecurePass1!\",\n  \"first_name\": \"Jane\",\n  \"last_name\": \"Smith\",\n  \"phone\": \"+15555555555\",\n  \"role\": \"doctor\",\n  \"specialty\": \"Internal Medicine\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/signup", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","v1","auth","signup"] },
            "description": "Register a new provider account.\n\n**Password requirements**: min 8 chars, at least 1 uppercase, 1 lowercase, 1 number.\n\n**Roles**: `doctor`, `nurse`, `admin`, `staff`\n\nIf `REQUIRE_EMAIL_VERIFICATION=true`, a verification email is sent and the account is locked until verified.\nIf `false` (default dev setting), login is allowed immediately."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "201 Created — Email Verification Required",
              "status": "Created", "code": 201,
              "body": "{\"message\": \"Account created. Please check your email to verify your account.\"}"
            },
            {
              "name": "201 Created — Direct Login (no verification)",
              "status": "Created", "code": 201,
              "body": "{\"access_token\": \"eyJ...\", \"token_type\": \"bearer\", \"user\": {\"id\": \"uuid\", \"email\": \"provider@hospital.org\", \"first_name\": \"Jane\", \"last_name\": \"Smith\", \"role\": \"doctor\"}}"
            },
            {
              "name": "409 Conflict — Email Already Exists",
              "status": "Conflict", "code": 409,
              "body": "{\"detail\": \"An account with this email already exists.\"}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (json.access_token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', json.access_token);",
                  "    pm.test('Login successful — token stored', () => true);",
                  "  } else if (json.mfa_required) {",
                  "    pm.test('MFA challenge required', () => true);",
                  "  }",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/x-www-form-urlencoded" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "urlencoded",
              "urlencoded": [
                { "key": "username", "value": "provider@hospital.org" },
                { "key": "password", "value": "SecurePass1!" }
              ]
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","v1","auth","login"] },
            "description": "OAuth2-compatible login using `application/x-www-form-urlencoded`.\n\n**Flow**:\n1. If email verification required and not verified → 403 error\n2. If MFA enabled → returns `{mfa_required: true, mfa_method: 'authenticator'|'sms'|'email'}` with no token\n3. If no MFA → returns JWT access_token immediately\n\nThe Test script auto-saves `access_token` to collection variables."
          },
          "response": [
            {
              "name": "200 OK — JWT token",
              "status": "OK", "code": 200,
              "body": "{\"access_token\": \"eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9...\", \"token_type\": \"bearer\", \"user\": {\"id\": \"uuid\", \"email\": \"provider@hospital.org\", \"first_name\": \"Jane\", \"role\": \"doctor\", \"mfa_enabled\": false}}"
            },
            {
              "name": "200 OK — MFA Required",
              "status": "OK", "code": 200,
              "body": "{\"mfa_required\": true, \"mfa_method\": \"authenticator\", \"message\": \"Enter your 6-digit TOTP code.\"}"
            },
            {
              "name": "401 Unauthorized — Wrong credentials",
              "status": "Unauthorized", "code": 401,
              "body": "{\"detail\": \"Invalid credentials.\"}"
            },
            {
              "name": "403 Forbidden — Email not verified",
              "status": "Forbidden", "code": 403,
              "body": "{\"detail\": \"Please verify your email before logging in.\"}"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "name": "Verify Email",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"token\": \"{{email_verification_token}}\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/verify-email", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","v1","auth","verify-email"] },
            "description": "Verify the email address using the token sent in the welcome/verification email.\n\nToken is included in the link: `{frontend_url}/verify-email?token=<token>`\n\nToken expires in 24 hours."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Resend Verification Email",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"provider@hospital.org\"\n}" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/resend-verification", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","v1","auth","resend-verification"] },
            "description": "Request a new verification email if the original expired or was not received."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Forgot Password",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"provider@hospital.org\"\n}" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/forgot-password", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","v1","auth","forgot-password"] },
            "description": "Sends a password reset link to the user's email. Token expires in 1 hour.\n\nAlways returns 200 (never reveals whether email exists — HIPAA security)."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Reset Password",
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"token\": \"{{password_reset_token}}\",\n  \"new_password\": \"NewSecurePass1!\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/reset-password", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","v1","auth","reset-password"] },
            "description": "Set a new password using the token from the reset email.\n\n**Password requirements**: min 8 chars, 1 uppercase, 1 lowercase, 1 number."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "MFA Setup — Initiate",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "bearer", "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{access_token}}" }] },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"method\": \"authenticator\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/mfa/setup", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","v1","auth","mfa","setup"] },
            "description": "Initiate MFA enrollment.\n\n**Methods**:\n- `authenticator` — TOTP (Google Authenticator, Authy, etc.) — returns QR code URL and secret\n- `sms` — SMS via Twilio — returns confirmation message\n- `email` — OTP to email\n\nAfter calling setup, user scans QR code and calls `/mfa/finalize` to confirm."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "MFA Setup — Finalize",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "bearer", "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{access_token}}" }] },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\n  \"code\": \"123456\"\n}" },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/mfa/finalize", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","v1","auth","mfa","finalize"] },
            "description": "Confirm MFA enrollment by submitting the first 6-digit TOTP code from the authenticator app.\n\nOnce finalized, MFA is enabled and will be required on all future logins."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "MFA Verify — During Login",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const json = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (json.access_token) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('access_token', json.access_token);",
                  "    pm.test('MFA verified — token stored', () => true);",
                  "  }",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"provider@hospital.org\",\n  \"code\": \"123456\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/mfa/verify", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","v1","auth","mfa","verify"] },
            "description": "Submit MFA code after the login challenge. Returns a full JWT access_token on success.\n\nTest script auto-saves the token."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Users",
      "description": "Current authenticated user profile management.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Get My Profile",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "bearer", "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{access_token}}" }] },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/users/me", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","v1","users","me"] },
            "description": "Returns the full profile of the currently authenticated user including organization memberships, role, specialty, NPI, MFA status."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Update My Profile",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "bearer", "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{access_token}}" }] },
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"first_name\": \"Jane\",\n  \"last_name\": \"Smith\",\n  \"phone\": \"+15555555555\",\n  \"specialty\": \"Cardiology\",\n  \"npi\": \"1234567890\",\n  \"provider_type\": \"MD\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/users/me", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","v1","users","me"] },
            "description": "Update the authenticated user's profile. All fields are optional (PATCH semantics). Supports both PUT and PATCH."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Change Password",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "bearer", "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{access_token}}" }] },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"current_password\": \"OldPass1!\",\n  \"new_password\": \"NewPass1!\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/users/me/password", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","v1","users","me","password"] },
            "description": "Change the authenticated user's password. Requires current password verification."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Patients",
      "description": "Patient registry management — CRUD operations on patient demographics.\n\nAll patient data is scoped to the authenticated user's organization.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List Patients",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const patients = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (patients.length > 0) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('patient_id', patients[0].id);",
                  "    pm.test('Patient list loaded — ID stored', () => true);",
                  "  }",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "bearer", "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{access_token}}" }] },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/patients?search=&status=active&skip=0&limit=50",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api","v1","patients"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "search", "value": "", "description": "Search by first name, last name, or email" },
                { "key": "status", "value": "active", "description": "Filter by status: active | inactive | deceased" },
                { "key": "skip", "value": "0" },
                { "key": "limit", "value": "50" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Returns paginated list of patients for the authenticated user's organization."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Create Patient",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  const patient = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('patient_id', patient.id);",
                  "  pm.test('Patient created — ID stored', () => true);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "bearer", "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{access_token}}" }] },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"first_name\": \"John\",\n  \"last_name\": \"Doe\",\n  \"email\": \"john.doe@email.com\",\n  \"phone\": \"+15555550001\",\n  \"date_of_birth\": \"1985-03-15\",\n  \"gender\": \"Male\",\n  \"address\": \"123 Main St\",\n  \"city\": \"Phoenix\",\n  \"state\": \"AZ\",\n  \"zip\": \"85001\",\n  \"race\": \"White\",\n  \"ethnicity\": \"Not Hispanic or Latino\",\n  \"preferred_language\": \"English\",\n  \"marital_status\": \"Married\",\n  \"mrn\": \"MRN-00001\",\n  \"status\": \"active\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/patients", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","v1","patients"] },
            "description": "Register a new patient. `mrn` (Medical Record Number) should be unique per organization.\n\nRequired: `first_name`, `last_name`\n\nDemographic fields (race, ethnicity, preferred_language) are required for ONC/CMS compliance reporting."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Recent Patients",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "bearer", "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{access_token}}" }] },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/patients/recent?limit=10",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api","v1","patients","recent"],
              "query": [{ "key": "limit", "value": "10" }]
            },
            "description": "Returns the most recently created patients (by created_at DESC). Useful for dashboard quick-access widgets."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Patient by ID",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "bearer", "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{access_token}}" }] },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/patients/{{patient_id}}", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","v1","patients","{{patient_id}}"] },
            "description": "Returns full patient demographics by UUID."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Update Patient",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "bearer", "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{access_token}}" }] },
            "method": "PUT",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"phone\": \"+15555550002\",\n  \"address\": \"456 New Ave\",\n  \"city\": \"Scottsdale\",\n  \"status\": \"active\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/patients/{{patient_id}}", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","v1","patients","{{patient_id}}"] },
            "description": "Update patient demographics. All fields optional."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Delete Patient",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "bearer", "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{access_token}}" }] },
            "method": "DELETE",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/patients/{{patient_id}}", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","v1","patients","{{patient_id}}"] },
            "description": "Permanently deletes the patient record. Returns 204 No Content.\n\n⚠️ HIPAA NOTE: Consider soft-deletion (status='inactive') for production systems to maintain audit trails."
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Appointments",
      "description": "Appointment scheduling — create, view, update, and cancel appointments.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "List Appointments",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "  const appts = pm.response.json();",
                  "  if (appts.length > 0) {",
                  "    pm.collectionVariables.set('appointment_id', appts[0].id);",
                  "  }",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "bearer", "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{access_token}}" }] },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/appointments?status=scheduled&date=2026-04-03",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api","v1","appointments"],
              "query": [
                { "key": "status", "value": "scheduled", "description": "scheduled | confirmed | in_progress | completed | cancelled | no_show" },
                { "key": "date", "value": "2026-04-03", "description": "Filter by date YYYY-MM-DD" },
                { "key": "skip", "value": "0" },
                { "key": "limit", "value": "100" }
              ]
            },
            "description": "Returns appointments for the authenticated provider. Filtered by status and/or date."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "My Appointments",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "bearer", "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{access_token}}" }] },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/appointments/me", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","v1","appointments","me"] },
            "description": "Returns the last 50 appointments for the currently authenticated provider, ordered by start_time DESC."
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Create Appointment",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "if (pm.response.code === 201) {",
                  "  const appt = pm.response.json();",
                  "  pm.collectionVariables.set('appointment_id', appt.id);",
                  "  pm.test('Appointment created', () => true);",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "bearer", "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{access_token}}" }] },
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"patient_id\": \"{{patient_id}}\",\n  \"patient_first_name\": \"John\",\n  \"patient_last_name\": \"Doe\",\n  \"start_time\": \"2026-04-10T09:00:00Z\",\n  \"end_time\": \"2026-04-10T09:30:00Z\",\n  \"duration_minutes\": 30,\n  \"visit_type\": \"Follow-up\",\n  \"room\": \"Exam Room 1\",\n  \"condition_type\": \"Chronic\",\n  \"reason\": \"Hypertension follow-up\",\n  \"status\": \"scheduled\",\n  \"location_type\": \"in-person\"\n}"
            },
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/appointments", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","v1","appointments"] },
            "description": "Create a new appointment.\n\n**Visit types**: `New Patient`, `Follow-up`, `Annual Exam`, `Sick Visit`, `Procedure`, `Telehealth`, `Consult`\n\n**Location types**: `in-person`, `telehealth`\n\n**Status**: `scheduled` (default), `confirmed`, `in_progress`, `completed`, `cancelled`, `no_show`"
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Get Appointment by ID",
          "request": {
            "auth": { "type": "bearer", "bearer": [{ "key": "token", "value": "{{access_token}}" }] },
            "method": "GET",
            "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/appointments/{{appointment_id}}", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api","v1","appointments","{{appointment_id}}"] }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "Update Appointment Status",
          "request": {
